com.gmail.woodyc40.commons.concurrent

Class Distributor<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gmail.woodyc40.commons.concurrent.Distributor<V>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - the return value of the Future representing the task submitted
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Callable<Future<V>>

    @ThreadSafe
public class Distributor<V>
extends Object
implements Callable<Future<V>>
    Distributes a task amongst a list of CountingExecutors, using a balancer and fallback ThreadPoolExecutors to assist with load estimates.
    Since:
    1.0
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:

      • call

        public Future<V> call()
               throws Exception
        Selects the worker to use

        The first step is to find the worker with the lowest work load

        The second step checks the work load of the lowest worker, if it is within 5% of 100, the fallback is selected

        However, if the fallback happens to be at 100% workload, then the task will be moved over to the balancer

        Specified by:
        call in interface Callable<Future<V>>
        Throws:
        Exception
